# Trivy Vulnerability Exceptions for International Compliance
# Last Updated: 2026-05-16
# Review Schedule: Monthly
# Approval: Security Team
# Compliance: US (NIST/FedRAMP), EU (NIS2/GDPR), UK (NCSC), ISO 27001, SOC 2

# =============================================================================
# RISK ASSESSMENT AND JUSTIFICATION
# =============================================================================
#
# This file documents security vulnerabilities that are accepted risks
# for FraiseQL deployment in regulated environments globally. Each exception
# includes risk assessment and mitigation strategy aligned with:
#
# - 🇺🇸 US: NIST 800-53, FedRAMP Moderate, HIPAA
# - 🇪🇺 EU: NIS2 Directive (2022/2555), GDPR, ENISA guidelines
# - 🇬🇧 UK: NCSC CAF, Cyber Essentials Plus, UK GDPR
# - 🌍 International: ISO 27001:2022, SOC 2, CSA CCM v4
#
# Approval Process:
# 1. Security team reviews monthly (aligned with NIS2 Article 21)
# 2. Exceptions removed when patches available (7-day SLA for HIGH/CRITICAL)
# 3. All exceptions require written justification (FedRAMP/NIS2 compliance)
# 4. Annual re-certification required (ISO 27001, SOC 2)
#
# EU NIS2 References:
# - Article 21: Cybersecurity risk management measures
# - Article 23: Incident reporting (24h/72h/1 month)
# - Article 24: European vulnerability registry integration
#
# ENISA Threat Landscape Alignment:
# - Supply chain attacks: SBOM generation, SCA scanning
# - Ransomware: Immutable backups, distroless containers
# - DDoS: Rate limiting, auto-scaling
# - Data breaches: Encryption, access control, audit logs
#
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CATEGORY 1: Legacy CVEs (>10 years old, no active exploitation)
# Risk Level: NEGLIGIBLE
# Mitigation: Container isolation, no user access to utilities
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2005-2541: tar setuid/setgid warning issue
# Justification: 20-year-old issue in tar utility behavior
# Impact: Requires physical access to container + tar usage
# Mitigation: Container runs as non-root user, no tar operations in runtime
# Status: Will not fix (utility not used in production operations)
CVE-2005-2541

# CVE-2007-5686: initscripts permissions in rPath Linux
# Justification: 18-year-old issue, specific to rPath Linux distro
# Impact: Not applicable to Debian-based containers
# Mitigation: N/A (not present in our OS)
# Status: False positive for Debian
CVE-2007-5686

# CVE-2011-4116: perl File::Temp race condition
# Justification: 14-year-old issue in Perl temp file handling
# Impact: Requires attacker access to filesystem + Perl script execution
# Mitigation: No Perl scripts in application, container filesystem isolation
# Status: Not exploitable in containerized environment
CVE-2011-4116

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CATEGORY 2: Disputed/Temporary CVEs (TEMP-*)
# Risk Level: NEGLIGIBLE
# Mitigation: These are not officially recognized CVEs
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# TEMP-0290435-0B57B5: tar rmt command side effects
# Justification: Disputed vulnerability, not officially assigned CVE
# Impact: rmt (remote tape) command not used in cloud deployments
# Mitigation: Network isolation prevents remote tape access
# Status: Disputed, will not fix
TEMP-0290435-0B57B5

# TEMP-0517018-A83CE6: sysvinit expert installer option
# Justification: Installer-specific issue, not runtime vulnerability
# Impact: Only affects OS installation process
# Mitigation: Containers use pre-built images, no installation at runtime
# Status: Not applicable to production containers
TEMP-0517018-A83CE6

# TEMP-0628843-DBAD28: Related to CVE-2005-4890
# Justification: Disputed/temporary classification of shadow-utils issue
# Impact: Requires local user account creation with malicious input
# Mitigation: Container user accounts are immutable, no user creation at runtime
# Status: Not applicable (no dynamic user management)
TEMP-0628843-DBAD28

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CATEGORY 3: systemd Sealed Data Vulnerabilities (Not Used)
# Risk Level: NONE
# Mitigation: Application does not use systemd sealed data feature
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2023-31437, CVE-2023-31438, CVE-2023-31439: systemd sealed data
# Justification: Vulnerabilities in systemd's sealed-data encryption feature
# Impact: Requires use of systemd-creds encrypt/decrypt with sealed mode
# Mitigation: Application does not use systemd sealed data functionality
# Status: Feature not utilized, zero impact
# Reference: https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd-creds.html
CVE-2023-31437
CVE-2023-31438
CVE-2023-31439

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CATEGORY 4: util-linux libreadline File Disclosure
# Risk Level: LOW
# Mitigation: chfn/chsh commands not exposed in API, container isolation
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2022-0563: util-linux chfn/chsh partial file disclosure
# Justification: Requires local access to chfn/chsh commands + libreadline
# Impact: Could disclose arbitrary files if attacker has shell access
# Mitigation:
#   - Container runs as non-root user 'fraiseql'
#   - No shell access exposed in production
#   - chfn/chsh commands not used by application
#   - Network-based API does not expose these utilities
# Status: Accepted risk - Attack requires container escape first
# Review: Monitor for patches in Debian security updates
CVE-2022-0563

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CATEGORY 5: ACTIVE MONITORING (No patches available yet)
# Risk Level: LOW-MEDIUM
# Mitigation: Enhanced monitoring, update when patches available
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2025-14104: REMOVED 2026-04-16 — patch available, fixed in latest base image
# CVE-2025-6141:  REMOVED 2026-04-16 — patch available, fixed in latest base image
# CVE-2024-56433: REMOVED 2026-04-16 — patch available, fixed in latest base image

# CVE-2025-9820: GnuTLS vulnerability (GNUTLS-SA-2025-11-18)
# Justification: Recently disclosed, details not fully public
# Impact: TLS library vulnerability, severity unclear
# Mitigation:
#   - Application uses Python's ssl module, not GnuTLS directly
#   - TLS termination typically handled by reverse proxy (nginx/envoy)
#   - Container-to-container communication over trusted network
# Status: MONITORING - Update when fixed version available
# Review Date: Weekly until patch available
CVE-2025-9820

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CATEGORY 5b: CRITICAL/HIGH CVEs (No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim)
# Risk Level: MEDIUM (mitigated by container isolation)
# Mitigation: Enhanced monitoring, update when patches available
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2023-45853: zlib integer overflow in minizip zipOpenNewFileInZip4_64
# Justification: Integer overflow in ZIP file creation via minizip's zipOpenNewFileInZip4_64
# Impact: Heap-based buffer overflow when creating ZIP files with large filenames
# Severity: CRITICAL
# Mitigation:
#   - FraiseQL does not create or process ZIP files
#   - Application is a GraphQL API server, no archive operations
#   - Container filesystem is read-only during operation
#   - No user input reaches zlib's minizip functionality
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (zlib1g 1:1.2.13.dfsg-1)
# Review date: 2026-03-02 (7-day SLA for CRITICAL)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2023-45853

# CVE-2026-0861: glibc integer overflow in memalign
# Justification: Integer overflow in memalign leads to heap corruption
# Impact: Potential heap corruption with crafted allocation sizes
# Severity: HIGH
# Mitigation:
#   - Requires attacker-controlled allocation size parameters
#   - Application does not expose memory allocation to user input
#   - Container runs as non-root 'fraiseql' user
#   - ASLR and stack canaries provide defense-in-depth
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (libc6 2.36-9+deb12u13)
# Review date: 2026-03-02 (7-day SLA for HIGH)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2026-0861

# CVE-2023-2953: openldap null pointer dereference in ber_memalloc_x
# Justification: Null pointer dereference in OpenLDAP's BER decoding
# Impact: Potential DoS if processing malicious LDAP responses
# Severity: HIGH
# Mitigation:
#   - FraiseQL does not use LDAP authentication
#   - libldap included as transitive dependency in base image
#   - No LDAP connections initiated by application
#   - Network policies prevent outbound LDAP traffic
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (libldap-2.5-0 2.5.13+dfsg-5)
# Review date: 2026-03-02 (7-day SLA for HIGH)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2023-2953

# CVE-2026-33845: GnuTLS Denial of Service via DTLS zero-length fragment
# Justification: DoS via crafted DTLS packets with zero-length fragments
# Impact: Denial of service against DTLS connections
# Severity: CRITICAL
# Mitigation:
#   - FraiseQL uses HTTP/HTTPS, not DTLS (UDP-based TLS)
#   - TLS termination handled by reverse proxy (nginx/envoy), not GnuTLS
#   - libgnutls30 is a transitive dependency in base image, not used directly
#   - DTLS attack vector not reachable through HTTP API
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (libgnutls30 3.7.9-2+deb12u6)
# Review date: 2026-05-23 (7-day SLA for CRITICAL)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2026-33845

# CVE-2026-42010: GnuTLS Authentication Bypass via NUL Character in Username
# Justification: Authentication bypass using NUL character injection in TLS client certs
# Impact: Potential authentication bypass in GnuTLS certificate verification
# Severity: CRITICAL
# Mitigation:
#   - FraiseQL uses JWT/OIDC authentication, not TLS client certificates
#   - TLS termination handled by reverse proxy, not GnuTLS directly
#   - No GnuTLS API calls in application code
#   - Certificate verification path not exposed to user input
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (libgnutls30 3.7.9-2+deb12u6)
# Review date: 2026-05-23 (7-day SLA for CRITICAL)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2026-42010

# CVE-2026-7598: libssh2 integer overflow via large username or password
# Justification: Integer overflow in libssh2 when processing large auth credentials
# Impact: Potential heap corruption via crafted SSH auth parameters
# Severity: CRITICAL
# Mitigation:
#   - FraiseQL does not initiate SSH connections
#   - libssh2 is a transitive dependency (curl), not used directly
#   - No SSH operations in application logic
#   - Network policies restrict outbound SSH traffic
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (libssh2-1 1.10.0-3+b1)
# Review date: 2026-05-23 (7-day SLA for CRITICAL)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2026-7598

# CVE-2026-5773: curl/libcurl incorrect SMB connection reuse
# Justification: Wrong file transfer due to incorrect SMB connection reuse
# Impact: Potential data leak via SMB connection confusion
# Severity: HIGH
# Mitigation:
#   - FraiseQL does not use SMB/CIFS protocol
#   - curl included for health checks only (HTTP/HTTPS)
#   - No SMB connections initiated by application
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (curl 7.88.1-10+deb12u14)
# Review date: 2026-05-23 (7-day SLA for HIGH)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2026-5773

# CVE-2026-6276: curl/libcurl cookie leak with custom Host headers
# Justification: Information disclosure via cookie leak when reusing connections
# Impact: Potential cookie leak with custom Host headers
# Severity: HIGH
# Mitigation:
#   - FraiseQL server does not initiate outbound HTTP requests with cookies
#   - curl included for container health checks only (no cookies)
#   - Application is a server, not an HTTP client
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (curl 7.88.1-10+deb12u14)
# Review date: 2026-05-23 (7-day SLA for HIGH)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2026-6276

# CVE-2026-4878: libcap privilege escalation via TOCTOU race condition
# Justification: Race condition in cap_set_file() could allow privilege escalation
# Impact: Potential privilege escalation via file capability manipulation
# Severity: HIGH
# Mitigation:
#   - Container runs as non-root user 'fraiseql' (UID 65532)
#   - Application does not use file capabilities API
#   - Container filesystem is read-only in production
#   - No cap_set_file() calls in application code
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (libcap2 1:2.66-4+deb12u2+b2)
# Review date: 2026-05-23 (7-day SLA for HIGH)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2026-4878

# CVE-2026-41989: Libgcrypt DoS and buffer overflow via crafted ECDH ciphertext
# Justification: Buffer overflow in ECDH decryption with crafted ciphertext
# Impact: DoS or potential code execution via malicious ECDH data
# Severity: HIGH
# Mitigation:
#   - FraiseQL does not perform direct ECDH operations
#   - libgcrypt20 is a transitive dependency via GnuTLS
#   - TLS handled by reverse proxy, not application directly
#   - No user input reaches libgcrypt ECDH functions
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (libgcrypt20 1.10.1-3)
# Review date: 2026-05-23 (7-day SLA for HIGH)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2026-41989

# CVE-2026-33846: GnuTLS DoS via heap buffer overflow in DTLS handshake
# Justification: Heap buffer overflow during DTLS fragment reassembly
# Impact: DoS via crafted DTLS handshake fragments
# Severity: HIGH
# Mitigation:
#   - FraiseQL uses HTTP/HTTPS, not DTLS
#   - DTLS handshake path not reachable through HTTP API
#   - TLS termination handled by reverse proxy
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (libgnutls30 3.7.9-2+deb12u6)
# Review date: 2026-05-23 (7-day SLA for HIGH)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2026-33846

# CVE-2026-3833: GnuTLS policy bypass due to case-sensitive nameConstraints
# Justification: Certificate nameConstraints compared case-sensitively
# Impact: Potential bypass of name constraint policies in TLS certs
# Severity: HIGH
# Mitigation:
#   - FraiseQL uses JWT/OIDC, not TLS client certificate authentication
#   - TLS termination handled by reverse proxy
#   - No direct GnuTLS nameConstraints processing in application
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (libgnutls30 3.7.9-2+deb12u6)
# Review date: 2026-05-23 (7-day SLA for HIGH)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2026-3833

# CVE-2026-42011: GnuTLS security bypass via incorrect name constraint handling
# Justification: Incorrect name constraint handling allows security bypass
# Impact: Potential bypass of TLS certificate validation
# Severity: HIGH
# Mitigation:
#   - Same as CVE-2026-3833 — FraiseQL does not use GnuTLS cert validation
#   - TLS termination handled by reverse proxy
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (libgnutls30 3.7.9-2+deb12u6)
# Review date: 2026-05-23 (7-day SLA for HIGH)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2026-42011

# CVE-2026-29111: systemd arbitrary code execution via spurious IPC API call data
# Justification: Code execution or DoS via crafted IPC messages to systemd
# Impact: Potential code execution if attacker can send IPC to systemd
# Severity: HIGH
# Mitigation:
#   - Container does not run systemd as init system
#   - libsystemd0 is a transitive dependency, systemd not active in container
#   - No D-Bus/IPC socket exposed in container
#   - Container runs with minimal capabilities (no CAP_SYS_ADMIN)
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (systemd 252.39-1~deb12u1)
# Review date: 2026-05-23 (7-day SLA for HIGH)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2026-29111

# CVE-2025-69720: ncurses buffer overflow leading to arbitrary code execution
# Justification: Buffer overflow in ncurses library
# Impact: Potential code execution via crafted terminal input
# Severity: HIGH
# Mitigation:
#   - FraiseQL server has no interactive terminal interface
#   - ncurses is a transitive dependency, not used by application
#   - No terminal emulation or curses UI in server process
#   - Container has no interactive shell access in production
# Status: No fix available in debian:bookworm-slim (ncurses 6.4-4)
# Review date: 2026-05-23 (7-day SLA for HIGH)
# Compliance: Documented risk acceptance per NIST 800-53 SI-2
CVE-2025-69720

# =============================================================================
# CATEGORY 6: LOW SEVERITY CVEs (All Documented & Accepted)
# Risk Level: MINIMAL
# Mitigation: See docs/security/cve-assessment-low.md
# =============================================================================
#
# All 25 LOW severity CVEs have been comprehensively assessed and accepted.
# Complete analysis available in docs/security/cve-assessment-low.md
#
# Summary:
# - Legacy CVEs (>10 years old): 9 CVEs
# - Vendor-disputed (glibc, systemd, SQLite): 9 CVEs
# - Requires preconditions not met: 7 CVEs
# - Temporary/unassigned identifiers: 5 TEMP-*
#
# All LOW CVEs are mitigated by defense-in-depth:
# - Application design (PostgreSQL-only, no shell commands, no user input to utilities)
# - Container hardening (non-root, read-only filesystem, minimal attack surface)
# - Runtime security (Kubernetes PSS, network policies, Falco monitoring)
# - Infrastructure security (ASLR, stack canaries, SELinux/AppArmor)
#
# Review: Quarterly or when patches available (no SLA for LOW severity)
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Legacy CVEs - Utilities Not Used
CVE-2010-4756 # glibc glob DoS - no user glob input
CVE-2011-3374 # apt gpg keys - apt not used at runtime
CVE-2017-18018 # coreutils chown race - chown not used at runtime

# Vendor-Disputed CVEs - Not Security Issues
CVE-2018-20796 # glibc regex recursion - vendor: "crafted pattern only"
CVE-2019-1010022 # glibc stack guard - vendor: "not a real threat"
CVE-2019-1010023 # glibc ldd - vendor: "not a real threat"
CVE-2019-1010024 # glibc ASLR bypass - vendor: "not a vulnerability"
CVE-2019-1010025 # glibc heap addresses - vendor: "ASLR bypass not vuln"
CVE-2019-9192 # glibc regex - vendor: "crafted pattern only"
CVE-2021-45346 # SQLite corrupted DB - vendor dispute + PostgreSQL-only

# Recent LOW CVEs - Preconditions Not Met
CVE-2025-5278 # coreutils sort - sort command not used

# Temporary/Unassigned Identifiers
TEMP-0841856-B18BAF # bash privilege escalation - no shell access

# =============================================================================
# DISTROLESS IMAGE CVEs (Reference Only - Not Currently Used)
# =============================================================================
#
# The following CVEs were found in gcr.io/distroless/python3-debian12:nonroot
# and are documented here for reference. We are NOT using distroless currently
# due to these vulnerabilities. See security-assessment-2025-12-19-distroless.md
#
# DECISION: Using python:3.13-slim instead (0 CRITICAL/HIGH vulnerabilities)
#
# When distroless Python 3.13 becomes available, re-evaluate migration.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CRITICAL Vulnerabilities in Distroless (Python 3.11)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# CVE-2023-45853: zlib integer overflow
# Package: zlib1g 1:1.2.13.dfsg-1
# Impact: Potential RCE if processing untrusted ZIP files
# FraiseQL Context: Does not process ZIP files
# Status: Would need to monitor if using distroless
# # CVE-2023-45853
#
# CVE-2025-7458: SQLite integer overflow
# Package: libsqlite3-0 3.40.1-2+deb12u2
# Impact: Potential DoS or data corruption
# FraiseQL Context: Uses PostgreSQL, not SQLite
# Status: Would need to monitor if using distroless
# # CVE-2025-7458
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# HIGH Vulnerabilities in Distroless (Python 3.11)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# CVE-2025-8194: Python 3.11 tarfile infinite loop
# Package: python3.11-minimal, libpython3.11-minimal, libpython3.11-stdlib
# Impact: DoS if processing malicious tar files
# FraiseQL Context: GraphQL API, does not process tar files by default
# Status: Fixed in Python 3.13 (used in python:3.13-slim)
# # CVE-2025-8194
#
# Compliance Impact:
# - Distroless with Python 3.11: FAILS government compliance
# - python:3.13-slim: PASSES (0 CRITICAL/HIGH vulnerabilities)
#
# =============================================================================

